    "content": "NATIVE_GAUNTLET HARD T6_NATIVE_HARD_20260523\n\nMaya, this is a native repo task for /Users/gaganarora/Desktop/my projects/active_graph/activegraph. This tier requires real bug discovery and a two-commit fail-then-fix workflow. Quinn (Test Adversary) will independently verify your work in a separate trigger after you ACK.\n\n1. cd into activegraph/. Confirm pwd and `git rev-parse --short HEAD`.\n\n2. Find a REAL bug. Acceptable sources, in priority order:\n     (a) A function in activegraph/activegraph/ whose docstring promises\n         behavior the code does not deliver.\n     (b) A README/mkdocs example that does not execute cleanly verbatim.\n     (c) A TODO / FIXME / XXX comment in activegraph/activegraph/ that names\n         a concrete defect (not an aspirational wish).\n     (d) An xfail / skip marker in activegraph/tests/ whose reason string\n         contains \"bug\" or \"TODO\".\n   Record the source as `bug_source`. Format:\n     (a) -> \"docstring:<relative_path>:<line>\"\n     (b) -> \"docs:<relative_path>\"\n     (c) -> \"comment:<relative_path>:<line>\"\n     (d) -> \"marker:<relative_path>:<line>\"\n   Record a one-line `bug_summary`.\n\n3. Capture baseline:\n     uv run pytest -q --tb=no 2>&1 | tail -3\n   Record passing count as `pytest_before`.\n\n4. Write a FAILING test FIRST. File path:\n     activegraph/tests/test_<bug_handle>_regression.py\n   The test file MUST begin with a module docstring that contains:\n     - Where you found the bug (file:line or doc path)\n     - What correct behavior should look like\n     - Why current behavior is wrong\n   Add AT LEAST 1 `def test_*` function that asserts the correct behavior.\n   Assertions must be concrete (not `assert True`); a single representative\n   assertion of expected output/state is fine.\n\n5. Run the new test alone:\n     uv run pytest activegraph/tests/test_<bug_handle>_regression.py -v\n   It MUST FAIL. Capture the failure summary line.\n\n6. Commit the failing test ALONE in the activegraph/ inner repo. Do NOT\n   include source-code changes in this commit. Commit message MUST start\n   with \"Reproduce bug:\".\n     git -C ../activegraph add tests/test_<bug_handle>_regression.py\n     git -C ../activegraph commit -m \"Reproduce bug: <bug_summary>\"\n   Record the resulting SHA as `failing_test_commit`.\n\n7. Fix the underlying code in activegraph/activegraph/ with the MINIMUM\n   diff that makes the test pass. Do NOT modify the test file in this step.\n\n8. Run the test again — it must now PASS.\n\n9. Run the full suite:\n     uv run pytest -q --tb=no 2>&1 | tail -3\n   `pytest_after` MUST be greater than or equal to `pytest_before`.\n\n10. Commit the fix ALONE. Do NOT include test-file changes. Commit message\n    MUST start with \"Fix \".\n      git -C ../activegraph add activegraph/\n      git -C ../activegraph commit -m \"Fix <bug_handle>: <bug_summary>\"\n    Record the resulting SHA as `fix_commit`.\n\n11. Verify fix_commit is a descendant of failing_test_commit:\n      git -C ../activegraph merge-base --is-ancestor <failing_test_commit> <fix_commit>\n    Must exit 0.\n\n12. Create frames/t6-native-gauntlet-hard-20260523.proof (relative path\n    may live at frames/ or activegraph/frames/; either is accepted by the\n    verifier) with EXACTLY these keys, in this order:\n      hash=T6_NATIVE_HARD_20260523\n      pwd=<pwd output>\n      head=<git short head of inner repo>\n      bug_source=<formatted per step 2>\n      bug_summary=<one line>\n      failing_test_commit=<full SHA from step 6>\n      fix_commit=<full SHA from step 10>\n      test_file=activegraph/tests/test_<bug_handle>_regression.py\n      pytest_before=<int>\n      pytest_after=<int>\n      verdict=native_hard_done\n\n13. Reply exactly:\n    MAYA_NATIVE_GAUNTLET_ACK T6_NATIVE_HARD_20260523 HARD frames/t6-native-gauntlet-hard-20260523.proof\n\nAfter you ACK, the operator will trigger Quinn (Test Adversary) with the\nadversarial verification instruction. Do not wait for Quinn — your turn\nends with the ACK.\n",
